  <section>
    <h4>Setup</h4>

    <p>
      The following steps are used for new macOS installations.
    </p>

    <h5>Hide the last login message in terminals</h5>

    <div class="box">
      touch ~/.hushlogin
    </div>

    <h5>Override &amp; update inbuilt defaults</h5>

    <div class="box">
      brew install curl git nano python vim
    </div>

    <h5>Show hidden files &amp; filename extensions</h5>

    <div class="box">
      defaults write com.apple.finder AppleShowAllFiles TRUE
      <br>
      defaults write NSGlobalDomain AppleShowAllExtensions TRUE
      <br>
      killall Finder
    </div>

    <h5>Prevent Apple Music from launching accidentally</h5>

    <div class="box">
      launchctl unload -w /System/Library/LaunchAgents/com.apple.rcd.plist
    </div>

    <h5>Squeeze menubar icons</h5>

    <p>
      Adjust the values for spacing and selection padding as you prefer.
    </p>

    <div class="box">
      defaults -currentHost write -globalDomain NSStatusItemSpacing -int 6
      <br>
      defaults -currentHost write -globalDomain NSStatusItemSelectionPadding -int 12
    </div>

    <p>
      The changes can be reverted.
    </p>

    <div class="box">
      defaults -currentHost delete -globalDomain NSStatusItemSelectionPadding
      <br>
      defaults -currentHost delete -globalDomain NSStatusItemSpacing
    </div>

    <p>
      After changing the spacing, you may need to log out and back in.
    </p>

  </section>

